          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
      Swiss rethink neutrality
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/swiss-neutrality-public-opinion-ukraine-war.jpg" alt="Despite the war in Ukraine, neutrality remains deeply rooted in Swiss public opinion." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
         Despite the war in Ukraine, neutrality remains deeply rooted in Swiss public opinion. Credits: Keystone / Laurent Gillieron </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       Switzerland is historically a neutral country, but the growing global instability and security concerns are partly <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-jun-25-spotlight-h1-1-influencing-public-opinion" target="_blank">influencing public opinion</a>. The optimism about the nation's future security has dropped to 69%. However, most people are questioning whether political and economic ties conflict with staying neutral.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
     For the first time, a narrow majority of around 53% <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-jun-25-spotlight-h1-2-favors-closer-cooperation" target="_blank">favors closer cooperation</a> with NATO. However, many still oppose hosting NATO military exercises or infrastructure in Switzerland. The support for the traditional army remains ‚Äùnecessary‚Äù, the backing for higher defence spending helped them secure $7.7B, the highest since 1986.  </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       There is strong backing for military modernization and support for gender-equal service obligations. Around 69% of them are in favor of retaining conscription, and 60% continue to support the militia system. </p>
        </mj-text>
