          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">
        Macron‚Äôs peace mission</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
      Summary: Emmanuel Macron proposes a demanding negotiated settlement to end the Israel-Iran conflict.</strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        French President Macron has tasked FM Jean-Noel Barrot to draft a demanding <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-jun-25-spotlight-h2-3-a-negotiated-settlement" target="_blank">a negotiated settlement</a> to resolve the rising conflict between Iran and Israel. Macron voiced deep concern over the increasing Israeli air strikes. Many targeted areas are not linked to Iran‚Äôs nuclear or missile programs and are causing more civilian casualties. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
            He also stressed the immediate need to end military actions that could bring further destruction to the region. Barrot will involve EU allies, German and British counterparts, reflecting a renewed European diplomatic effort. France, the UK, and Germany were previously involved in talks that led to a landmark <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/what-iran-nuclear-deal" target="_blank">2015 nuclear agreement</a>. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Meanwhile, Iran‚Äôs FM Abbas Araghchi confirmed that he will be meeting the FMs of France, Germany, and the UK in Geneva. Shortly after that, he will travel to Istanbul to attend the meeting of the Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC). Araghchi will <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-jun-25-spotlight-h2-4-participate-in-talks" target="_blank">participate in talks</a> concerning the ongoing Israeli conflict against the Islamic Republic.</p>
        
