      <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/global-diplomacy-map-rwanda-pakistan-finland-russia.jpg" alt="Flags representing geopolitical connections between the Czech Republic, Rwanda, Pakistan, Finland and Russia are shown spanning a world map" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
      <mj-spacer height="10px"/>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá®üáø Czech Republic -  Government survives scandal.</strong> 
           Czech PM Petr Fiala‚Äôs government survived a no-confidence vote after a scandal involving a $45M bitcoin donation from a convicted drug dealer to the Justice Ministry. Former Justice Minister Pavel Bla≈æek resigned amid the controversy (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-jun-25-worldwide-7-bitcoin-scandals" target="_blank">bitcoin scandals</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá∑üáº Rwanda - Peace agreement drafted.</strong> 
           Rwanda and the DR Congo have initiated a draft peace agreement, backed by the US, aiming to end the fighting in eastern Congo. The agreement includes a ceasefire, disarmament of armed groups, and a joint security mechanism. A full signing is set for June 27 (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-jun-25-worldwide-8-more-about-the-agreement" target="_blank">more about the agreement</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáµüá∞ Pakistan - White House visit.</strong> 
           President Trump hosted Pakistan‚Äôs army chief, signaling a strategic reset in US-Pakistan relations, with a focus on counterterrorism and regional stability. However, bypassing civilian leadership highlights military dominance, raising concerns over democracy and the transactional nature of this renewed engagement (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-jun-25-worldwide-9-about-the-meeting" target="_blank">about the meeting</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>üá´üáÆ Finland - Landmine treaty.</strong> 
          Finland‚Äôs parliament has voted to withdraw from the Ottawa Convention banning anti-personnel landmines, citing increased security concerns from Russia. President Stubb and DM Hakkanen defended the move, calling it necessary for national defense (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://www.euronews.com/2025/06/19/finlands-parliament-votes-to-withdraw-from-landmine-treaty-due-to-russia-threat" target="_blank">the details</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>üá∑üá∫ Russia - Drills with China.</strong> 
