What is the Strait of Hormuz, and why is it relevant?
 
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/strait-of-hormuz-oil-transport-gateway.jpg" alt="The Strait of Hormuz is considered the world's most important gateway for oil transport." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
          <i>The Strait of Hormuz is considered the world's most important gateway for oil transport.</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         The Strait of Hormuz is situated between the Persian Gulf and the Gulf of Oman. The narrow passage connects the oil-rich Middle East to global markets, with around 20-25% of the world‚Äôs oil flowing through it. The 21-mile-wide waterway is a vital route for energy exports from countries such as Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, and Iraq.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">     
       The ongoing conflict between Israel and Iran has put this waterway into focus. Iran's control over the northern entrance of the strait makes it a potential target. However, while Iran has the military tools to disrupt shipping, a full closure is unlikely without provoking a primary US allied military response. 
        </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">     
      The US Navy has a significant presence in the area. They have not promised involvement yet, but should it enter a war with Iran, this strait would be a chokehold. Any disruption can cause <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-jun-25-foundations-h1-12-oil-worth-to-spike" target="_blank">oil worth to spike</a> and create market instability. 
        </p>
